Rebalancing can lower risk.Portfolio Volatility - Hypothetical Moderate Asset Allocation.Risk is based on the standard deviation of a hypothetical moderate asset allocation (35% large-cap stocks, 15% international stocks, 10% small-cap stocks, 35% bonds, and 5% cash investments), rebalanced annually, from 1970 to 2015. Source: Schwab Center for Financial Research, with data from Morningstar, Inc.
Tax Efficient.
